results.name: n-th arithmetic derivative of n.
comment: a(n) is zero for all prime n.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..80
mathematica: dn[0]=0; dn[1]=0; dn[n_] := Module[{f=Transpose[FactorInteger[n]]}, If[PrimeQ[n], 1, Plus@@(n*f[[2]]/f[[1]])]]; Table[Nest[dn,n,n], {n,50}]
results.author: _José María Grau Ribas_, Jan 24 2012
